reviewText: Assignment are too confusing. Material is very dry and does not help with the assignments. The challenging assignments lead to not having enough peer reviews to receive a grade.

T​he idea of having students rate your essays is terrible. For the amount of money this website costs per month, it should be marked by an actual instructor - even if they are not a specialist in that field. I generally get HD's for my essays at uni, but for some reason students think they deserve an F here. It seems like the only solution is what other students are doing in the forums - asking for a perfect grade in return for the same.

Highly recommend for anyone looking to learn more about/gain a better appreciation of agriculture, soil and water systems, sustainable practices and triple bottom line thinking.

Undoubtingly, defining agricultural sustainability, as with every other sustainability concept, is a challenging task. Nevertheless, it is a common agreement that agricultural sustainability should at least address the three basic pillars of sustainable development by appraising simultaneously environmental, economic, and social issues related to agricultural practices. However, the sustainability assessment of agricultural practices, in general, can be a very challenging task since it involves many case-specific variables to be taken under consideration  .This course addressed all the issues of Sustainable Agricultural Land management.
